Q: Laravel Vue Inertia delete confirm returning modal with &quot;1&quot; value A: <p>Use a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code></p>
<pre><code>&lt;tr v-for=&quot;articleCategory in articleCategories.data&quot; :key=&quot;articleCategory.id&quot;&gt;
  &lt;td&gt;{{ articleCategory.title }}&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;td&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;flex gap-2 justify-end&quot;&gt;
      &lt;TableEditButton :href=&quot;route('article_categories.edit', articleCategory.id)&quot; /&gt;
      &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; @click=&quot;destroy(articleCategory.id)&quot;&gt;
        Delete
      &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>But if is necessary to use <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> add .prevent</p>
<pre><code>&lt;Link href=&quot;#&quot; @click.prevent=&quot;destroy(articleCategory.id)&quot;&gt;Delete&lt;/Link&gt;
</code></pre>

Q: Google Apps Script how to get &quot;live&quot; data? A: <pre><code>function fetchStockPCR() {
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActive();
  const listSheet = ss.getSheetByName(&quot;STOCK_LIST&quot;);
  const liveSheet = ss.getSheetByName(&quot;STOCK_PCR_LIVE&quot;);
  const histSheet = ss.getSheetByName(&quot;STOCK_PCR_HISTORY&quot;);

  const stocks = listSheet.getRange(2,1,listSheet.getLastRow()-1,2).getValues();
  liveSheet.getRange(&quot;A2:F100&quot;).clearContent();

  let row = 2;

  stocks.forEach(stock =&gt; {
    const symbol = stock[0];
    const enabled = stock[1];

    if (enabled !== &quot;YES&quot;) return;

    const url = `https://www.nseindia.com/api/option-chain-equities?symbol=${symbol}`;
    const options = {
      method: &quot;get&quot;,
      headers: {
        &quot;User-Agent&quot;: &quot;Mozilla/5.0&quot;,
        &quot;Accept-Language&quot;: &quot;en-US,en;q=0.9&quot;
      },
      muteHttpExceptions: true
    };

    try {
      const response = UrlFetchApp.fetch(url, options);
      const data = JSON.parse(response.getContentText());

      let ceVol = 0, peVol = 0;

      data.records.data.forEach(r =&gt; {
        if (r.CE) ceVol += r.CE.totalTradedVolume || 0;
        if (r.PE) peVol += r.PE.totalTradedVolume || 0;
      });

      const pcr = peVol / ceVol;
      let signal = &quot;⚪ RANGE&quot;;

      if (pcr &gt; 1.2) signal = &quot;🟢 BULLISH&quot;;
      if (pcr &lt; 0.8) signal = &quot;🔴 BEARISH&quot;;

      liveSheet.getRange(row,1,1,6)
        .setValues([[symbol, ceVol, peVol, pcr.toFixed(2), signal, new Date()]]);

      histSheet.appendRow([new Date(), symbol, pcr.toFixed(2)]);

      row++;

    } catch (e) {
      Logger.log(symbol + &quot; error&quot;);
    }
  });
}
</code></pre>

Q: Error &#39;UNABLE_TO_GET_ISSUER_CERT_LOCALLY&#39; A: <p>This error can come when we are calling a https from a local system.</p>
<p><strong>For Nest.JS application</strong></p>
<p>Go to your, app.module.ts, add the code for HttpModule as shown below</p>
<pre><code>import { HttpModule } from &quot;@nestjs/axios&quot;;

@Module({
  imports: HttpModule.register({
    // Create an HTTPS agent to ignore SSL certificate errors
    httpsAgent: new (require('https').Agent)({
      rejectUnauthorized: false,
    })})],
  controllers: [..........],
  providers: [.........],
})
export class AppModule {}
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> it's safe to have environment variable check for this rejectUnauthorised:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre><code>rejectUnauthorized: process.env.NODE_ENV == &quot;dev&quot; ? false : true
</code></pre>
